The paper discusses the security of SCADA systems, which are used in industrial control systems (ICS). This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a statistical fingerprinting technique, which involves analyzing data patterns, which could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of security policies, which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
